pageContext.claim: “We sell a car in China, which by the way, is almost impossible to do despite the tax, it's 25 percent.”
pageContext.analysis: It's not "nearly impossible" for U.S. automakers to sell cars in China. General Motors sells more cars in China (3.9 million) than in the US (3 million) and saw its China business grow 13 percent in 2016.
